explanation: Uses reverse DP to count how many floors can be covered with m moves and k eggs, avoiding the O(k n²) DP table. The inner loop updates dp[eggs] = dp[eggs] + dp[eggs-1] + 1, representing the sum of floors covered if the egg breaks or survives. The loop stops once dp[k] ≥ n, giving the minimal m.

